    What is the most valuable Monet painting?
    Meules (Haystacks)
    Meules (Haystacks), 1890-1891

    Not only did Meules take the cake on validating the value of the French Impressionist, the bid on this piece made it the first Impressionist piece to surpass $100 Million! Meules is one of eight pieces left in private hands from the entirety of the Haystacks series.

    Which Monet painting was in Titanic?
    'Water Lilies', Claude Monet

    One of the most famous Impressionist works ever created, Claude Monet's Water Lilies were brought to an even wider audience by the film Titanic. The painting was supposedly brought onto the ship by Rose, Kate Winslet's character in the film.

    Why is Monet so popular?
    His influence on modern art is profound, inspiring movements like Post-Impressionism and Abstract Expressionism. Overall, Monet's ability to blend technique, emotion, and innovative ideas makes his paintings timeless and highly regarded within the art world.Jun 26, 2017

    Overview

    Description

    Oscar-Claude Monet was a French painter and founder of Impressionism painting who is seen as a key precursor to modernism, especially in his attempts to paint nature as he perceived it. Wikipedia
    Born: November 14, 1840, Rue Laffitte, Paris, France
    Died: December 5, 1926 (age 86 years), Giverny, France
    Periods: Impressionism, Modern art
    Influenced by: Pierre-Auguste Renoir, Camille Pissarro See more
    Spouse: Alice Hosched (m. 18921911), Camille Doncieux (m. 18701879)
    Education: Acadmie Suisse (18591860) See more
